text.tspan: Gap in GDP per hour worked with respect to the United States, 1970 to 2016
Figure illustrates the gap in GDP per hour worked with respect to the United States. The gap is calculated by taking a country's GDP per hour
worked minus that of the US, divided by US GDP per hour worked. A positive gap suggests the country is more productive (has higher GDP
per hour worked) than the US.
Data source: OECD - Productivity - Level of GDP per capita and productivity
